SIMPLE: stowage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stowage
<hw>Stow"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
or method of stowing; <as>as, the <ex>stowage</ex> of provisions in a
vessel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Room in which things may be stowed.</def>
<rj><au>Cook.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In every vessel is <qex>stowage</qex> for immense treasures.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The state of being stowed, or put away.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧To have them in safe <xex>stowage</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Things stowed or packed.</def> <rj><au>Beau. &
Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Money paid for stowing goods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stowaway</ent>⟦br⟧
